from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s_o8dwzRlu4



Control Plane (can have multiple master nodes control planes for redudancy)
  1.API Server (entry point to K8s - UI, API, CLI)
  2. Controller Manager (Keeps track of whats happening to the cluster)
  3. Scheduler (ensures pods placement)
  4. etcd (holds the current state of the K8s state - backing store)

Worker Nodes (virtual or physical machine)

Pod: abstraction over a container
A Node contains Pods
A Pod usually runs one container
A Service is an IP address assigned to a Pot
External Service: accessible from outside world, Internal Service accessible only internally from K8s
Ingress takes the url of the app and forwards it to the Internal Service ip

